    "VARIABLES": "Let x be the number of patients whose temperature is taken by the electronic thermometer, and y be the number of patients whose temperature is taken by the regular thermometer. Both x and y are non-negative integers.",
    "CONSTRAINTS": "1. x \geq 2y: At least twice as many patients should have their temperature checked by the electronic thermometer than the regular thermometer. 2. y \geq 50: At least 50 patients should have their temperature checked by a regular thermometer. 3. 3x + 2y \leq 15000: Total time taken by both thermometers should not exceed the total time the office is open.",
    "OBJECTIVE": "Maximize x + y: Maximize the number of patients whose temperature can be taken."
